In a speech at the U.S. Capitol Visitor Center, President Joe Biden expressed gratitude for the support he received during difficult times and acknowledged the strength of those who face challenges without the same support. He shared a personal conversation with his late son Beau, who asked him to promise to stay engaged in politics. Biden emphasized the importance of staying connected and getting to know one another, even in times of disagreement. He reflected on the power of prayer and unity, especially in the face of division and violence. The President also mentioned recent acts of unity and compassion in the face of tragedy, highlighting the role that faith can play in bringing people together. He called on leaders to protect democracy and work together to make a positive impact. Biden expressed hope for a united America and quoted an Irish poet, saying that there is a chance to make hope and history rhyme. He concluded by urging everyone to keep the faith and spread it to others.